bilingual.source: Do you want to buy a ticket to become an astronaut?

bilingual.source: I have bought my ticket so you can take the train.
bilingual.target: 我已经买了票，所以你可以坐火车。

bilingual.source: Please bring your student card if you want a cheap ticket.

yingyinNormal.en: Tickets, please. Pedro's lost his ticket again.
yingyinNormal.zh: 请把票拿出来。佩德罗又把他的票弄丢了。

yingyinNormal.en: What do you think about giving Sheldon's ticket to Stuart?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们觉得把谢尔顿的票给斯尔图特怎么样？

yingyinNormal.en: Tickets, please. Mr Rabbit has come to check everyone's ticket.
yingyinNormal.zh: 请出示车票。兔先生已经要开始检查大家的票了。

yingyinNormal.en: Unbelievable detail. Ticket. May I see your ticket？
yingyinNormal.zh: 这细节刻画地真赞。您的车票，请出示您的车票。

yingyinNormal.en: I gave notice. Ticket. Notice？May I see your ticket？
yingyinNormal.zh: 我提出申请了。您的车票。什么申请？请出示您的车票。

yingyinNormal.en: There's Pedro's ticket. Oh, that's where I put it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩德罗的车票在这里。哦，原来我把它放在这里了。

yingyinNormal.en: Owners of ticket and non-owner of the ticket, that are not different in any other way.
yingyinNormal.zh: 得到票的人和没得到票的人，除此之外他们没有任何其他不同。

yingyinNormal.en: How many tickets? One Mummy ticket and two little Piggies. And one fish please. The fish goes free.
yingyinNormal.zh: 需要几张票呢？一张成人票还有两张儿童票。还有一张金鱼票，谢谢。金鱼可以免费。

yingyinNormal.en: Tickets, please. Mr Rabbit has come to check everyone's ticket. I think I've lost my ticket. Oh, dear lord, dear.
yingyinNormal.zh: 检票了。兔先生过来检查大家的火车票了。我想我的票弄丢了。噢，太不小心了。

yingyinNormal.en: I think I've lost my ticket. Oh, dear lord, dear. Meow, there's your ticket. Pedro, you are sitting on it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我觉得我的票丢了。哦，天哪，亲爱的。喵喵，你的票在这里。佩德罗，你做在它上面呢！

yingyinNormal.en: Now, children, do not lose these tickets. Can I see your tickets, please? I've lost my ticket.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好了，孩子们，你们不要把票弄丢哦。请把你们的票拿出来。噢，我的票弄丢了。

yingyinNormal.en: Can I have a ticket, please? The blue ticket wins a toy car. Well done, Danny.
yingyinNormal.zh: 兔小姐我想要抽一张！蓝色的票赢得一辆……玩具车！真不错，丹尼。

yingyinNormal.en: The last minute fare on this ticket is twenty seven hundred dollars.
yingyinNormal.zh: 临时票的价钱是2700元。

yingyinNormal.en: A ticket cost money. How do we get money? Mom's purse.
yingyinNormal.zh: 票是要钱的，我们怎么弄到钱？老妈的钱包。

yingyinNormal.en: Pedro, can I have my hat back, please? There's Pedro's ticket. Oh, that's where I put it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩德罗，能把帽子还给我了吗？佩德罗的票在这呢。噢，原来我把我的票放在这了。

yingyinNormal.en: The first one is the students who owned a ticket they were not willing to part with it for less than $1400 average.
yingyinNormal.zh: 第一个是有票的学生都不愿意以低于1400美元的价格出让他们的票。

yingyinNormal.en: It's also the place to snap up a half-price ticket to a Broadway show.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这里也是抢购百老汇表演半价票的地方。

yingyinNormal.en: Ticket？Are we gonna make up the ten minute？We gonna try, Sir.
yingyinNormal.zh: 您的票。晚点的十分钟能追回来吧。先生，我们尽量。

yingyinNormal.en: I bought a ticket from a man who would likely be dead if it wasn't for you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我从一个人手里买了张票，倘若不是你他可能已经死了。

yingyinNormal.en: The people who did not have a ticket were not willing to pay an average more than $170.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而那些没票的人则不愿以高于170美元的价格买入。
